{
  "stem": "20083.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, of course, we actually went to the Dutch embassy, too, and experienced the same misery, so to speak.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because there were always long lines.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, as you know, quite a few German Jews did go emigrate to Holland, including the, Anne Frank's family.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then we tried Belgium and even England, but it was absolutely hopeless.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then somehow, my mother got hold of-- heard of a woman, Berlin, a German Quaker woman, who was very much interested in getting Jews out of Germany.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Her name was Mrs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Elizabeth Landmann, Frau Elizabeth Landmann.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she visited my mother one day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I think it was either December 1938 or January 1939.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And she suggested that I should I join a Kindertransport, a children's transport.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "These children's transport, transports started immediately after the Kristallnacht and lasted for about 11 months altogether, saving approximately 10,000 Jewish children from Nazi Germany and Austria.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And she suggested that I put my name down, and that if I was lucky, I could emigrate without a passport.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, she was sent by somebody.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I do not remember or do not know who sent her, but she appeared one day at our doorstep.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we simply asked her what she wanted.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she explained.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she said, I heard from somebody so-and-so that your son is trying to get out and your daughter, too.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when she heard that my daughter was 10 years older than I was--",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I'm so sorry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm so sorry.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Yeah, my, my sister Anne Marie was 10 years older than I.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But she no longer qualified to be a member of the Kindertransport.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
